{
  "text": "In other words, the DoF of a full SO(3) is three. Note that a rotational matrix can alternatively be represented by the Euler angles decomposition [CITATION_1] . A bijective mapping \u2228 : so(3) \u2192 R 3 and its reverse mapping \u2227 : R 3 \u2192 so(3) are defined as\u03c9 \u2228 = \u03c9, and \u03c9 \u2227 =\u03c9, respectively. Let \u03bd \u2208 R 3 , an element of se(3) can then be identified a\u015d",
